New Records: Adam Zampa became the tournament’s leading wicket-taker
Key Match Events: Mitchell Starc strangled Jonny Bairstow down the leg side off the very first ball
Adam Zampa took an absolute stunner in Ahmedabad
Ben Stokes fell to Adam Zampa, letting out a howling 'no!' as he swept a catch to Marcus Stoinis
David Warner took the catch in the deep off Adam Zampa to send the last recognised England batter back to the hutch for 42
Post-Match Reflections: The Australian team returned to the field of play after the interval wearing black armbands in memory of Mitchell March's grandfather Ross, who passed away on Friday
Mitch Marsh, having flown home to be with his family, will rejoin the squad in Mumbai by Monday
Miscellaneous Highlights: Australia remain in contention of a semi-final spot with their fifth-win in a row
England’s sixth defeat finally sees them mathematically out of contention to finish in the top four
Australia failed to build on the 75-run partnership from 96 balls between Steve Smith and Marnus Labuschagne
Adam Zampa came to an end when he was caught behind off Woakes for 29, and Mitchell Starc was the final wicket to fall two deliveries later when he was caught by Moeen in the circle
Others: Innings highlights of the England-Australia clash at the ICC Men's Cricket World Cup 2023
